The article is a transcript of a press briefing call on the Edward M. Kennedy Serve America Act. The Act is a sweeping expansion of national service programs in the United States, aimed at increasing volunteerism and civic participation. The call was led by Melody Barnes, Director of the White House Domestic Policy Council, Alan Solomont, Chair of the Corporation for National and Community Service, and Stephen Goldsmith, Vice Chair of the Corporation for National and Community Service. They discussed the initiatives that the Act will support, including increasing the number of AmeriCorps members from 75,000 to 250,000 by 2017, expanding service programs in education, healthcare, clean energy, and veterans services, and establishing a social innovation fund. The speakers emphasized the bipartisan support for the legislation and the importance of service in addressing the nation's challenges. They also discussed the need to support nonprofit organizations and the impact of service on individuals and communities.